<p>I went down to where he writes â€œNow letâ€™s edit your public key:â€ (though weâ€™re really about to edit the private keys). As instructed, in terminal I typed: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">gpg --edit-key 03FC30EE</code>, which will first display information about the public keys associated with this key.</p>

